  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop the <strong>tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>waxy potatoes </strong>and <strong>halved tomatoes</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, drizzle with <strong>olive oil </strong>and season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the dish in the oven for an initial 25 min</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657621754417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657621754417-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657621754417-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657621754417-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1657621754417-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, use a sharp knife to cut a deep pocket along the top of the <strong>chicken breast portions </strong>(be careful not to cut all the way through!)</p><p>Fill the pockets with the<strong> 'Nduja </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!), then season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – these are your '<strong>Nduja stuffed chicken breasts</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1657621781027-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
